# Initialiser List


## Initializer List Constructor
An initializer list constructor initializes member variables before the body of the constructor is executed. 
This approach is often more efficient, especially for initializing constants or reference members, 
and for initializing members with non-default constructors.


#include <iostream>
#include <string>

class BankAccount {
private:
    string accountNumber;
    int balance;

public:
    // Initializer list constructor
    BankAccount(string accNum, int bal)
        : accountNumber(accNum), balance(bal) {}

    void checkBalance() const {
        cout << "Balance: " << balance << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    BankAccount account("123456789", 1000);
    account.checkBalance();
    return 0;
}
